{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So I want to tell you a story -- an encouraging story --"},{"time":4000,"text":"about addressing"},{"time":6000,"text":"desperation, depression and despair in Afghanistan,"},{"time":9000,"text":"and what we have learned from it,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and how to help people"},{"time":13000,"text":"to overcome traumatic experiences"},{"time":17000,"text":"and how to help them to regain some confidence"},{"time":20000,"text":"in the time ahead -- in the future --"},{"time":22000,"text":"and how to participate again in everyday life."},{"time":26000,"text":"So, I am a Jungian psychoanalyst,"},{"time":28000,"text":"and I went to Afghanistan in January 2004, by chance,"},{"time":32000,"text":"on an assignment for Medica Mondiale."},{"time":35000,"text":"Jung in Afghanistan --"},{"time":37000,"text":"you get the picture."},{"time":40000,"text":"Afghanistan is one of the poorest countries in the world,"},{"time":43000,"text":"and 70 percent of the people are illiterate."},{"time":46000,"text":"War and malnutrition kills people"},{"time":48000,"text":"together with hope."},{"time":50000,"text":"You may know this from the media,"},{"time":52000,"text":"but what you may not know"},{"time":54000,"text":"is that the average age of the Afghan people is 17 years old,"},{"time":57000,"text":"which means they grow up in such an environment"},{"time":60000,"text":"and -- I repeat myself --"},{"time":62000,"text":"in 30 years of war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"So this translates"},{"time":66000,"text":"into ongoing violence,"},{"time":68000,"text":"foreign interests, bribery,"},{"time":70000,"text":"drugs, ethnic conflicts,"},{"time":73000,"text":"bad health, shame, fear"},{"time":76000,"text":"and cumulative traumatic experiences."},{"time":79000,"text":"Local and foreign military"},{"time":81000,"text":"are supposed to build peace together with the donors"},{"time":84000,"text":"and the governmental and non-governmental organizations."},{"time":87000,"text":"And people had hope, yes,"},{"time":89000,"text":"but until they realized"},{"time":91000,"text":"their situation worsens every day --"},{"time":93000,"text":"either because they are being killed"},{"time":95000,"text":"or because, somehow,"},{"time":98000,"text":"they are poorer than eight years ago."},{"time":101000,"text":"One figure for that:"},{"time":103000,"text":"54 percent of the children under the age of five years"},{"time":106000,"text":"suffer from malnutrition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"Yet, there is hope."},{"time":111000,"text":"One day a man told me,"},{"time":113000,"text":"\"My future does not look brilliant,"},{"time":115000,"text":"but I want to have a brilliant future for my son.\""},{"time":119000,"text":"This is a picture I took in 2005,"},{"time":121000,"text":"walking on Fridays over the hills in Kabul,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and for me it's a symbolic picture"},{"time":126000,"text":"of an open future for a young generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"So, doctors prescribe medication."},{"time":136000,"text":"And donors"},{"time":138000,"text":"are supposed to bring peace"},{"time":140000,"text":"by building schools and roads."},{"time":145000,"text":"Military collect weapons,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and depression stays intact."},{"time":150000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":152000,"text":"Because people don't have tools"},{"time":154000,"text":"to cope with it, to get over it."},{"time":159000,"text":"So, soon after my arrival,"},{"time":161000,"text":"I had confirmed something which I had already known;"},{"time":164000,"text":"that my instruments come from the heart of modern Europe, yes."},{"time":167000,"text":"However, what can wound us"},{"time":169000,"text":"and our reaction to those wounds --"},{"time":171000,"text":"they are universal."},{"time":173000,"text":"And the big challenge"},{"time":175000,"text":"was how to understand the meaning of the symptom"},{"time":178000,"text":"in this specific cultural context."},{"time":181000,"text":"After a counseling session, a woman said to me,"},{"time":184000,"text":"\"Because you have felt me, I can feel myself again,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and I want to participate again"},{"time":189000,"text":"in my family life.\""},{"time":192000,"text":"This was very important,"},{"time":194000,"text":"because the family is central"},{"time":196000,"text":"in Afghans' social system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"No one can survive alone."},{"time":202000,"text":"And if people feel used, worthless and ashamed,"},{"time":205000,"text":"because something horrible has happened to them,"},{"time":208000,"text":"then they retreat, and they fall into social isolation,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and they do not dare to tell this evil"},{"time":214000,"text":"to other people or to their loved ones,"},{"time":217000,"text":"because they do not want to burden them."},{"time":219000,"text":"And very often violence is a way to cope with it."},{"time":223000,"text":"Traumatized people also easily lose control --"},{"time":226000,"text":"symptoms are hyper-arousal and memory flashbacks --"},{"time":228000,"text":"so people are in a constant fear"},{"time":230000,"text":"that those horrible feelings of that traumatic event"},{"time":233000,"text":"might come back unexpectedly,"},{"time":235000,"text":"suddenly,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and they cannot control it."},{"time":240000,"text":"To compensate this loss of inner control,"},{"time":243000,"text":"they try to control the outside,"},{"time":246000,"text":"very understandably -- mostly the family --"},{"time":248000,"text":"and unfortunately,"},{"time":250000,"text":"this fits very well"},{"time":252000,"text":"into the traditional side,"},{"time":255000,"text":"regressive side, repressive side,"},{"time":257000,"text":"restrictive side of the cultural context."},{"time":261000,"text":"So, husbands start beating wives,"},{"time":264000,"text":"mothers and fathers beat their children,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and afterward, they feel awful."},{"time":268000,"text":"They did not want to do this, it just happened --"},{"time":270000,"text":"they lost control."},{"time":273000,"text":"The desperate try"},{"time":275000,"text":"to restore order and normality,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and if we are not able to cut this circle of violence,"},{"time":282000,"text":"it will be transferred to the next generation without a doubt."},{"time":285000,"text":"And partly this is already happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"So everybody needs a sense for the future,"},{"time":291000,"text":"and the Afghan sense of the future"},{"time":293000,"text":"is shattered."},{"time":297000,"text":"But let me repeat the words of the woman."},{"time":300000,"text":"\"Because you have felt me,"},{"time":302000,"text":"I can feel myself again.\""},{"time":305000,"text":"So the key here is empathy."},{"time":307000,"text":"Somebody has to be a witness"},{"time":309000,"text":"to what has happened to you."},{"time":311000,"text":"Somebody has to feel how you felt."},{"time":314000,"text":"And somebody has to see you and listen to you."},{"time":319000,"text":"Everybody must be able"},{"time":321000,"text":"to know what he or she has experienced is true,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and this only goes with another person."},{"time":328000,"text":"So everybody must be able to say,"},{"time":330000,"text":"\"This happened to me, and it did this with me,"},{"time":333000,"text":"but I'm able to live with it, to cope with it,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and to learn from it."},{"time":337000,"text":"And I want to engage myself"},{"time":339000,"text":"in the bright future for my children"},{"time":341000,"text":"and the children of my children,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and I will not marry-off my 13 year-old daughter,\" --"},{"time":346000,"text":"what happens too often in Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"So something can be done,"},{"time":351000,"text":"even in such extreme environments as Afghanistan."},{"time":354000,"text":"And I started thinking about a counseling program."},{"time":357000,"text":"But, of course, I needed help and funds."},{"time":359000,"text":"And one evening,"},{"time":361000,"text":"I was sitting next to a very nice gentleman in Kabul,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and he asked what I thought would be good in Afghanistan."},{"time":366000,"text":"And I explained to him quickly,"},{"time":368000,"text":"I would train psycho-social counselors,"},{"time":371000,"text":"I would open centers, and I explained to him why."},{"time":375000,"text":"This man gave me his contact details at the end of the evening"},{"time":378000,"text":"and said, \"If you want to do this, call me.\""},{"time":381000,"text":"At that time, it was the head of Caritas Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"So, I was able to launch a three-year project with Caritas Germany,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and we trained 30 Afghan women and men,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and we opened 15 counseling centers in Kabul."},{"time":394000,"text":"This was our sign -- it's hand-painted,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and we had 45 all over Kabul."},{"time":400000,"text":"Eleven thousand people came -- more than that."},{"time":402000,"text":"And 70 percent regained their lives."},{"time":405000,"text":"This was a very exciting time,"},{"time":407000,"text":"developing this with my wonderful Afghan team."},{"time":410000,"text":"And they are working with me up to today."},{"time":412000,"text":"We developed a culturally-sensitive"},{"time":414000,"text":"psycho-social counseling approach."},{"time":417000,"text":"So, from 2008 up until today,"},{"time":420000,"text":"a substantial change and step forward"},{"time":422000,"text":"has been taking place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"The European Union delegation in Kabul"},{"time":427000,"text":"came into this and hired me to work"},{"time":429000,"text":"inside the Ministry of Public Health,"},{"time":431000,"text":"to lobby this approach --"},{"time":433000,"text":"we succeeded."},{"time":435000,"text":"We revised the mental health component"},{"time":438000,"text":"of the primary health care services"},{"time":440000,"text":"by adding psycho-social care"},{"time":442000,"text":"and psycho-social counselors to the system."},{"time":445000,"text":"This means, certainly, to retrain all health staff."},{"time":448000,"text":"But for that, we already have the training manuals,"},{"time":451000,"text":"which are approved by the Ministry"},{"time":454000,"text":"and moreover, this approach is now part"},{"time":456000,"text":"of the mental health strategy in Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"So we also have implemented it already"},{"time":462000,"text":"in some selected clinics in three provinces,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and you are the first to see the results."},{"time":468000,"text":"We wanted to know if what is being done is effective."},{"time":471000,"text":"And here you can see"},{"time":473000,"text":"the patients all had symptoms of depression,"},{"time":476000,"text":"moderate and severe."},{"time":479000,"text":"And the red line is the treatment as usual --"},{"time":481000,"text":"medication with a medical doctor."},{"time":483000,"text":"And all the symptoms"},{"time":485000,"text":"stayed the same or even got worse."},{"time":488000,"text":"And the green line is treatment with psycho-social counseling only,"},{"time":490000,"text":"without medication."},{"time":492000,"text":"And you can see the symptoms almost completely go away,"},{"time":495000,"text":"and the psycho-social stress has dropped significantly,"},{"time":498000,"text":"which is explicable,"},{"time":500000,"text":"because you cannot take away the psycho-social stresses,"},{"time":502000,"text":"but you can learn how to cope with them."},{"time":505000,"text":"So this makes us very happy,"},{"time":507000,"text":"because now we also have some evidence"},{"time":509000,"text":"that this is working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"So here you see,"},{"time":514000,"text":"this is a health facility in Northern Afghanistan,"},{"time":516000,"text":"and every morning it looks like this all over."},{"time":519000,"text":"And doctors usually have three to six minutes for the patients,"},{"time":522000,"text":"but now this will change."},{"time":524000,"text":"They go to the clinics,"},{"time":526000,"text":"because they want to cure their immediate symptoms,"},{"time":528000,"text":"and they will find somebody to talk to"},{"time":530000,"text":"and discuss these issues"},{"time":532000,"text":"and talk about what is burdening them"},{"time":534000,"text":"and find solutions, develop their resources,"},{"time":537000,"text":"learn tools to solve their family conflicts"},{"time":541000,"text":"and gain some confidence in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"And I would like to share one short vignette."},{"time":548000,"text":"One Hazara said to his Pashtun counselor,"},{"time":552000,"text":"\"If we were to have met some years ago,"},{"time":555000,"text":"then we would have killed each other."},{"time":557000,"text":"And now you are helping me"},{"time":559000,"text":"to regain some confidence in the future.\""},{"time":562000,"text":"And another counselor said to me after the training,"},{"time":565000,"text":"\"You know, I never knew why I survived the killings in my village,"},{"time":569000,"text":"but now I know,"},{"time":571000,"text":"because I am part of a nucleus"},{"time":573000,"text":"of a new peaceful society in Afghanistan.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"So I believe this kept me running."},{"time":579000,"text":"And this is a really emancipatory and political contribution"},{"time":582000,"text":"to peace and reconciliation."},{"time":585000,"text":"And also -- I think --"},{"time":587000,"text":"without psycho-social therapy,"},{"time":589000,"text":"and without considering this"},{"time":591000,"text":"in all humanitarian projects,"},{"time":593000,"text":"we cannot build-up civil societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"I thought it was an idea worth spreading,"},{"time":599000,"text":"and I think it must be,"},{"time":601000,"text":"can be, could be replicated elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604000,"text":"I thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}